## Architecture Patterns

### Async/Await Standards
```[PRIMARY_LANGUAGE]
# Good - Proper async patterns
async def process_data(data):
    """Process data with proper async handling."""
    try:
        result = await external_service.process(data)
        await cache.store(result)
        return result
    except Exception as e:
        logger.error(f"Processing failed: {e}")
        raise

# Bad - Blocking operations in async context
async def bad_process(data):
    time.sleep(1)  # ❌ Blocking call
    return sync_operation(data)  # ❌ Sync in async
```

